{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"OpdCi2T7nWRqHDhKARCDP","title":"Negative Sampling","desc":"","updated":1642349823093,"created":1642349473050,"custom":{},"fname":"science.math.Optimization.Optimizers In in Neural Networks.Negative Sampling","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"8851c7ba0567617f00328d18cce61ede","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"science.math.Optimization.Optimizers In in Neural Networks.Negative Sampling","id":"OpdCi2T7nWRqHDhKARCDP","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"science.stats.Deep Neural Networks.Language Models","alias":"science.stats.Deep Neural Networks.Language Models","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":83,"offset":232},"end":{"line":5,"column":147,"offset":296},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"science.stats.Deep Neural Networks.Language Models","anchorHeader":"^word2vec"}},{"from":{"fname":"engineering.system_design.ML System Design.Recommender Systems","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":216,"column":6,"offset":5365},"end":{"line":216,"column":86,"offset":5445},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Optimizers In in Neural Networks.Negative Sampling","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Optimizers In in Neural Networks.Negative Sampling"},{"from":{"fname":"science.stats.Regression.Recommender Systems.Implicit Data Handling","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":83,"offset":516},"end":{"line":12,"column":163,"offset":596},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Optimizers In in Neural Networks.Negative Sampling","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Optimizers In in Neural Networks.Negative Sampling"}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"gz71FnqSIo2TfwivaD4Df","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"negative-sampling\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#negative-sampling\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Negative Sampling</h1>\n<p>In a context where finally we have a 'classifier' that outputs a one-hot vector,\nwe have essencially a large-cardinality multinomial distribution.</p>\n<p>the likelyhood has terms then for all possible categories. They can be many (e.g. <a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/sx92oju973uydTM0c39Cv#^word2vec\">Language Models</a>).</p>\n<p>Then, to speed up things, we pretend for this training example only that the multinomial distribution\nis much smaller (e.g. pick 5 random 'negative' examples).\nThen compute the loss and corresponding gradients (for this iteration) based on that.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://mccormickml.com/2017/01/11/word2vec-tutorial-part-2-negative-sampling/#:~:text=Negative%20sampling%20addresses%20this%20by%20having%20each%20training,output%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20network%20is%20a%20one-hot%20vector.\">Source: Mccormickml tutorial</a></p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/QE1BddXlccbyYN1avaB4M\">Recommender Systems</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/QTHWXTVUZOxYZPVJ0eh7Y\">Implicit Data Handling</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1647507231129,"created":1631901573363,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"db285659ccac8b133c384de1ef51de66","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-stefans-notes":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to Stefan's Notes!","value":"welcome-to-stefans-notes","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["mxzxxu8z4e6krz99ht96y9d","W1EOZ27Tqx6RbiA2aW3DI","DyoLE2kwm9rRfRZhBGxPW","idhfogizmtcmvaamtalp3o3","4w8wBCSRvYUnGIZeozW03","vB321AipYCs6ldVC0APs9","h6WVdl1UTWVXeWuMJSZ1f","bth6m0exy9q9loxib1mc4al","4abAmH56ausbldEJbZokx","JyOFJ5NTPSVWMfiDy951X","0OO7fjCpcaGZg5qDRZr8z","138666663","pohXgII67dAxnoufG7yAP","42r6290iqzLPmg9BY7fIp","3hoLerNJHjNkDziIKlFF2","T6meT3UNw0nRorEbzoPSl","hIOTXIIBj3vmhG1xc91lA","tnFlQuOAGPkbU2fZI7Cb1","Jb3w3f4x